{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"6703","heading":"Definitions","label":"6703 Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/ch86","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","References in TextThe Forest and Rangeland Renewable Resources Planning Act of 1974, referred to in par. (1)(B), is , , , which is classified generally to subchapter I (§ 1600 et seq.) of chapter 36 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 93–37888 Stat. 476section 1600 of this titleAug. 17, 1974"],"amendments":["References in TextThe Forest and Rangeland Renewable Resources Planning Act of 1974, referred to in par. (1)(B), is , , , which is classified generally to subchapter I (§ 1600 et seq.) of chapter 36 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Short Title note set out under and Tables.Pub. L. 93–37888 Stat. 476section 1600 of this titleAug. 17, 1974"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Adaptive ecosystem management","label":"1 Adaptive ecosystem management","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"Definition","label":"A Definition","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is based on scientific findings and the needs of society;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"treats management actions as experiments;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/A/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F1%2FA%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"acknowledges the complexity of these systems and scientific uncertainty; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/A/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F1%2FA%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"uses the resulting new knowledge to modify future management methods and policy.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Clarification","label":"B Clarification","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"This paragraph shall not define the term “adaptive ecosystem management” for the purposes of the Forest and Rangeland Renewable Resources Planning Act of 1974 ( et seq.).16 U.S.C. 1600","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Affected entities","label":"2 Affected entities","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"land managers;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"stakeholders;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"concerned citizens; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/2/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F2%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the States of the interior West, including political subdivisions of the States.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"Dry forest and woodland ecosystem","label":"3 Dry forest and woodland ecosystem","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “dry forest and woodland ecosystem” means an ecosystem that is dominated by ponderosa pines and associated dry forest and woodland types.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"Institute","label":"4 Institute","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Institute” means an Institute established under .section 6704(a) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":"Interior West","label":"5 Interior West","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “interior West” means the States of Arizona, Colorado, Idaho, Nevada, New Mexico, and Utah.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":"Land manager","label":"6 Land manager","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/6/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F6%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “land manager” means a person or entity that practices or guides natural resource management.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Inclusions","label":"B Inclusions","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/6/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F6%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “land manager” includes a Federal, State, local, or tribal land management agency.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":"Restoration","label":"7 Restoration","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/7/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F7%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a sustainable structure of the ecosystem or habitat; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/7/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/7","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F7%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a condition that supports a natural complement of species, natural function, or ecological process (such as a low-intensity fire).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":"Secretary","label":"8 Secretary","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of Agriculture, acting through the Chief of the Forest Service.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":"Secretaries","label":"9 Secretaries","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/9","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F9","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/9/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/9","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F9%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Secretary of Agriculture, acting through the Chief of the Forest Service; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/9/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/9","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F9%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Secretary of the Interior.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"10","heading":"Stakeholder","label":"10 Stakeholder","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/10","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F10","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “stakeholder” means any person interested in or affected by management of forest or woodland ecosystems.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"11","heading":"Subdominant trees","label":"11 Subdominant trees","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/11","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F11","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Are trees that occur underneath the canopy or extend into the canopy but are smaller and less vigorous than dominant trees.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"12","heading":"Overstocked stands","label":"12 Overstocked stands","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/12","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F12","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Where the number of trees per acre exceeds the natural carrying capacity of the site.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"13","heading":"Resilience","label":"13 Resilience","identifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703/13","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t16/s6703","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft16%2Fs6703%2F13","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The ability of a system to absorb disturbance without being pushed into a different, possibly less desirable stable state.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}
